# CountDown Project Structure Guide

## Landing Page (LP)
The landing page is a static website built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

### Key Files
- Main page: [index.html](mdc:LP/index.html)
- Styles: [css/style.css](mdc:LP/css/style.css)
- JavaScript: [js/main.js](mdc:LP/js/main.js)
- Legal documents:
  - [privacy_policy.html](mdc:LP/privacy_policy.html)
  - [terms_of_service.html](mdc:LP/terms_of_service.html)
  - [support.html](mdc:LP/support.html)

### Configuration
- Firebase config: [.firebaserc](mdc:LP/.firebaserc)
- Firebase hosting config: [firebase.json](mdc:LP/firebase.json)

## Server
The server directory contains Firebase Cloud Functions and configuration.

### Key Files
- Firebase config: [.firebaserc](mdc:server/.firebaserc)
- Firebase hosting config: [firebase.json](mdc:server/firebase.json)
- Firestore rules: [firestore.rules](mdc:server/firestore.rules)
- Firestore indexes: [firestore.indexes.json](mdc:server/firestore.indexes.json)

## Project Structure
```
countDown/
├── LP/                    # Landing page files
│   ├── css/              # Stylesheets
│   ├── js/               # JavaScript files
│   ├── images/           # Image assets
│   └── *.html           # HTML pages
├── server/               # Firebase server files
│   └── functions/        # Cloud Functions
└── countDown/            # iOS app source
```

## Deployment
- Landing page is deployed to Firebase Hosting
- Server functions are deployed to Firebase Cloud Functions
- App is published on the App Store

